MBOMBELA –  According to department of Safety, Security and Liaison spokesman Joseph Mabuza, the accident occurred at around 02:30. An eye-witness at the scene said a Nissan Navarro was travelling towards Barberton when an old Honda Ballade  allegedly made a U-Turn in the road. “The bakkie collided into the Honda. The Honda Ballade basically split in half with the impact.”  The eye-witness stated that there had been a man and a woman and a child in the Honda Ballade. “The child had died on the scene and the rest had been taken to hospital. Mabuza said the Ballade had a Mozambican registration number plate. “We believe the parents are in hospital and are from Mozambique.” 